abstract: SAN DIEGO, Sept. 10 (AP)--Fred Dean, the San Diego Chargers' outstanding but unhappy defensive end, has formally filed for retirement.
headline_main: Dean Quits, Says Chargers Won't Discuss Grievance
headline_print_headline: Dean Quits, Says Chargers Won't Discuss Grievance

abstract: Marty Bystrom, a tall right-hander who joined the Phillies a little more than a week ago in the annual September rookie invasion of the major leagues, experienced one of baseball's supreme thrills last night. He pitched a shutout in his first big league start, beating the Mets, 5-0, at Shea Stadium.

PRINCESS MARGARET, Sean Connery, Pete Fountain and Joanne Woodward. What do they have in common? They  all turned 50 years old this year, according to the monthly birthday column in the magazine 50 Plus, which now considers them to be eligible for a genre of magazines directed specifically to America's older citizens.
headline_main: Magazines That Tap The Over-50 Market
headline_print_headline: Magazines That Tap The Over-50 Market

abstract: NEW BRUNSWICK, N.J. Sept. 8-- Reaching out to a constituency that he said could be critical to the success of his bid for the Presidency, Representative John B. Anderson took his independent candidacy to a series of college campuses in the Northeast today, ending up this evening at Rutgers, the State University.
headline_main: Anderson Hails Campus 'Awakening'; Students Back His Positions Remarks on Social Security Waiting for Debate Decision
headline_print_headline: Anderson Hails Campus 'Awakening'; Students Back His Positions Remarks on Social Security Waiting for Debate Decision

abstract: LOS ANGELES, Sept. 7--Ed Asner won his seventh Emmy--for best actor in a dramatic series, "Lou Grant"--last night at the 32d annual Emmy Awards show. Because of an actors' boycott, Mr. Asner was not there to pick up his award.
headline_main: Emmys to Asner, Miss Damon, Miss Bel Geddes and Mulligan

abstract: Even though Dave Wilson had satisfied the University of Illinois coaching staff that he was the player to start at quarterback this season, he still had to win a court battle before getting permission to play in the opening game last Saturday against Northwestern.
